        </figure>
        <figure id="f1602724" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602724.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"/>
            <caption>Figure 24. Arrow indicates Spindle Shaft</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>Mark spindle shaft and plate to aid in later assembly.</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1602725" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602725.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px"/>
            <caption>Figure 25. Remove Steering Wheel</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>Use wheel puller to loosen steering wheel from spindle shaft. Remove steering wheel from
                    spindle.
                </callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1602726" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602726.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"/>
            <caption>Figure 26. Clock Spring</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. Clock Spring Body</callout1>
                <callout1>2. Clock Spring Harness</callout1>
                <callout1>3. Spindle</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1602727" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602727.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"/>
            <caption>Figure 27. Clock Spring with Details and Harness</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. Remove screws from tabs. (see arrows)</callout1>
                <callout1>2. Remove clock spring.</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1602728" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602728.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"/>
            <caption>Figure 28. Clock Spring with Harnesses</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>Disconnect the clock spring harness from the dash harness.</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1602729" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602729.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"/>
            <caption>Figure 29. Cruise Control Module Removal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. To remove the cruise control modules slide them toward the center and lift out.</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>
            <title>STEERING WHEEL INSTALLATION</title>
        </para>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Read and follow the Clock Spring Installations instructions very carefully. IF THE CLOCK SPRING IS
                    NOT INSTALLED CORRECTLY IT WILL BREAK IN USE.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f1602730" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figG16/G1602730.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"/>
            <caption>Figure 30. Clock Spring and Harnesses</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>Connect the clock spring harness to the dash harness.</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1602731" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602731.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"/>
            <caption>Figure 31. Clock Spring Detail</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. Clock Spring Body</callout1>
                <callout1>2. Retainer Clip</callout1>
                <callout1>3. Alignment Arrow on tab</callout1>
                <callout1>4. Alignment Arrow on Clock Spring Body</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>Install the clock spring using the alignment arrows on the clock spring body (4) and on the tab (3). To
            assure that the clock spring is properly centered, do the following:
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn the spring 3 1/2 turns counter clockwise.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Return the spring 3 1/2 turns clockwise.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn the spring 3 1/2
                <emph type="bold">additional</emph>turns clockwise.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Return the spring 3 1/2 turns counter clockwise to the center.</para>
        </step1>
        <para>If no binding has occurred the spring is now centered. If binding occurs, rotate the clock spring body
            appropriately and repeat steps until no binding occurs through 3 1/2 turns in each direction from center
            (seven turns lock-to-lock).
        </para>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">IF THE CLOCK SPRING BINDS IT WILL BREAK IN USE!</emph>
        </para>
        <figure id="f1602732" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figG16/G1602732.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"/>
            <caption>Figure 32. Clock Spring Installed with Detail</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. Clock Spring Body</callout1>
                <callout1>2. Clock Spring Wire Harness</callout1>
                <callout1>3. Spindle Shaft</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1602733" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602733.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"/>
            <caption>Figure 33. Wheel Installed Over Spindle</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>Line up marks made earlier (if applicable) to aid in alignment.</para>
        <figure id="f1602734" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602734.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"/>
            <caption>Figure 34. Install Spindle Nut</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1602735" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602735.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"/>
            <caption>Figure 35. Locking Clip</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>Assure that the locking clip is properly located to prevent it working loose.</para>
        <figure id="f1602736" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602736.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"/>
            <caption>Figure 36. Side Covers Seen From Below</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. Turn Signal Lever</callout1>
                <callout1>2. Side Covers</callout1>
                <callout1>3. Retaining Bolt</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1602737" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602737.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"/>
            <caption>Figure 37. Install Front Cover</caption>
        </figure>
